ed a remarkably unified secular alternative to traditional religion. Woodson-Boulton raises provocative questions about the meaning and use of art in relation to artistic practice, urban development, social justice, education, and class. In today's context of global austerity and shrinking government support of public cultural institutions, this book is a timely consideration of arts policy and purposes in modern society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aArt and societyzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aArt and societyzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aArt and statezGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aArt and statezGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aArt museumszGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aArt museumszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804780537zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780537423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804780537.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles